    "title_en": "Does QFT make sense in non-integer dimensions?",
    "abstract_en": "We revisit the old problem of analytically continuing QFTs to fractional dimension $d\\in\\mathbb C$. We observe that common theories like QCD and QED have branch cuts in the complex $d$ plane. In particular, many operators in their low-energy CFT have OPEs and scaling dimensions that jump as a function of $d$.",
